ive.org/details/woodrowwilsonpr00link online]\n* {{cite book |last1=Weisman |first1=Steven R. |title=The Great Tax Wars: Lincoln to Wilson-The Fierce Battles over Money That Transformed the Nation |date=2002 |publisher=Simon & Schuster |isbn=978-0-684-85068-9 |url=https://archive.org/details/greattaxwars00weis }}\n{{refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{Main|Bibliography of Woodrow Wilson}}\n{{Too much further reading|date=February 2019}}\n{{Refbegin|2}}\n\n===Surveys===\n\n* Keene, Jennifer D. ''The United States and the First World War'' (Routledge, 2014).\n* Link, Arthur S. ''Woodrow Wilson and the progressive era, 1910-1917'' (1954).\n* Slosson, Preston W. ''The Great Crusade And After (1914-1928)'' (1930), Scholarly survey of social history  [https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.188413 online]\n* Young, Ernest William. ''The Wilson Administration and the Great War'' (1922) [https://archive.org/details/wilsonadministr00youngoog online edition]\n* Venzon, Anne ed. ''The United States in the First World War: An Encyclopedia'' (1995), Very thorough coverage.\n* Zieger, Robert H. ''America's Great War: World War I and the American Experience'' 2000. 272 pp.\n\n===Biographical===\n\n* Blum,  John Morton. ''Joe Tumulty and the Wilson Era'' (1951).\n* Cooper, John Milton. ''Woodrow Wilson'' (2009), A major scholarly biography.\n* Craig, Douglas B. ''Progressives at War: William G. McAdoo and Newton D. Baker, 1863\u20131941'' (2013).\n* Kazin, Michael. ''A Godly Hero: The Life of William Jennings Bryan'' (2006). [https://www.amazon.com/Godly-Hero-William-Jennings-Bryan/dp/0375411356/  excerpt]\n* Link, Arthur S. \"Woodrow Wilson\" in Henry F. Graff ed., ''The Presidents: A Reference History '' (2002) pp.&nbsp;365\u2013388; [https://www.presidentprofiles.com// online] short scholarly biography; Link's 5 volume biography ends in April 1917\n* Neu, Charles E. ''Colonel House: A Biography of Woodrow Wilson's Silent Partner'' (Oxford UP, 2015), 699 pp\n* Shook, Dale N.