ctions of Peace during War: The Lloyd George Government's Reactions to Woodrow Wilson, December, 1916-November, 1918|journal=Transactions of the American Philosophical Society|volume=65|issue=2|pages=1\u2013117|year=1975|last1=Kernek|first1=Sterling J.}}\n''Transactions of the American Philosophical Society'' 65 (April 1975): 7\u201327; \n* Knock, Thomas J. ''To End All Wars: Woodrow Wilson and the Quest for a New World Order'' (Princeton UP, 1992).\n* Levin Jr., N. Gordon. ''Woodrow Wilson and World Politics: America's Response to War and Revolution'' (Oxford UP, 1968), New Left approach.\n* Link, Arthur S. ''Wilson the Diplomatist: A Look at His Major Foreign Policies'' (1957) [http://hdl.handle.net/2027/mdp.39015004819630 online]\n* Link, Arthur S.; ''Woodrow Wilson and a Revolutionary World, 1913\u20131921'' (1982)\n* Meyer  G.J. ''The World Remade: America In World War I'' (2017), popular survey, 672pp\n* Neu, Charles E. ''Colonel House: A Biography of Woodrow Wilson's Silent Partner'' (2014); Scholarly biography [https://networks.h-net.org/node/20317/reviews/73264/rowlett-neu-colonel-house-biography-woodrow-wilsons-silent-partner online review]\n* {{cite book|doi=10.1007/978-3-319-50457-5_3|chapter=Woodrow Wilson Versus Henry Cabot Lodge: The Battle over the League of Nations, 1918\u20131920|title=American Presidential Statecraft|pages=67\u2013111|year=2017|last1=Powaski|first1=Ronald E.|isbn=978-3-319-50456-8}}\n* Quirk, Robert E. ''An affair of honor: Woodrow Wilson and the occupation of Veracruz'' (1962). on Mexico\n* Startt, James D. ''Woodrow Wilson, the Great War, and the Fourth Estate'' (Texas A&M UP, 2017) 420 pp. \n*  Stevenson, David. ''The First World War and International Politics'' (1991), Covers the diplomacy of all the major powers.\n* {{cite journal|doi=10.1017/S0021875800015310|title=Woodrow Wilson and World War I: A Reappraisal|journal=Journal of American Studies|volume=19|issue=3|pages=325\u2013348|year=1985|last1=Thompson|first1=J. A.}}\n* 